result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason A Palms was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Bond previously posted in the amount of $350 has been applied. Remaining costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant is entitled to Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges.

Request for reduction in payment plan-Courts response

Return on Warrants - All Cases Called @ 1:07 PM: Defendant Jason A Palms in court, in custody, appears via video.  Ruth Ann Zouski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Per Atty Zouski:  Has had no contact from Def.  Only time a payment is made is if we have a warrant in place.  Statement by Def as to unpaid matters - states he just lost his job and has no funds to post for release.  The Court:  Finds basis exists for contempt due to lack of payments made.  Imposes 90 days WCJ - Stayed - Purge:  Make an initial payment for release from jail of $200.00 with a payment plan in the amount of $100 due the first of each month, to commence 10/1/2016.  Further statement by Defendant as to amounts owed.  Corp Counsel confirms $936.50 is the outstanding balance owed.  $200 must be paid up from release from WCJ.  Considering that the amount is outstanding is less Court reduces the initial payment - a good faith downpayment of $100.00 must be paid up front for release.
